    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>137</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>098700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Νικα-"><seg part="I">Νικα<choice><unclear>γ</unclear><unclear>ι</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear></choice></seg><gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/></name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκά<supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></w> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέθηκε</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2a"/><space quantity="3" unit="line"/>                
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app>
                        <lem>Νικα<choice><unclear>γ</unclear><unclear>ι</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear></choice><gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">Νικα<unclear>ι</unclear><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem>δεκά<supplied reason="lost">ταν ἀνέθηκε</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">δεκά<supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></rdg>
                 </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Nika<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">a consacré</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">ce monument</supplied> au titre de la dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Nica<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">dedicated</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">this monument</supplied> as a tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Nika<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">ha dedicato</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">questo monumento</supplied> come decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>A reduced formula <foreign xml:lang="grc">τῶ δεῖνος δεκάτα</foreign> would be conceivable, but is never attested. With the nominative we only have the type <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάτα τὠπόλλωνος</foreign> scratched on sherds. So it is preferable, on a support like this one, to restore a formula with verb + accusative,
                which furthermore provides space for name and father's name at line 1. From it, before the break, there remains only a tiny lower part of a hasta. There are a lot of possibilities for the restoration of the first name with the three possible letters 
                    that we have selected amongst more numerous ones which would have given no plausible result.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
